%% AutomationOS Process State Machine
%% Mermaid State Diagram

stateDiagram-v2
    [*] --> CREATED: process_create()

    CREATED --> READY: scheduler_add_process()
    note right of CREATED
        Process just created
        • PCB allocated
        • Stack allocated
        • Page tables setup
        • Not yet scheduled
    end note

    READY --> RUNNING: schedule() selects process
    note right of READY
        Ready to run
        • In scheduler queue
        • Waiting for CPU time
        • Context saved
    end note

    RUNNING --> READY: Time slice expired (timer IRQ)
    RUNNING --> BLOCKED: I/O request or sleep()
    RUNNING --> TERMINATED: exit() syscall
    note right of RUNNING
        Currently executing
        • Has CPU time
        • Running on core
        • time_slice > 0
    end note

    BLOCKED --> READY: I/O complete or wakeup
    note right of BLOCKED
        Waiting for event
        • I/O operation
        • Sleep timeout
        • Signal from another process
        • Not in scheduler queue
    end note

    TERMINATED --> [*]: process_destroy()
    note right of TERMINATED
        Zombie state
        • Exit status saved
        • Waiting for parent wait()
        • Resources not yet freed
        • PCB kept for parent
    end note

    %% State transitions with detailed labels
    state RUNNING {
        [*] --> ExecutingUser: From READY
        ExecutingUser --> ExecutingKernel: syscall/interrupt
        ExecutingKernel --> ExecutingUser: return to userspace
    }

    state BLOCKED {
        [*] --> WaitingIO: I/O request
        [*] --> Sleeping: sleep() syscall
        [*] --> WaitingChild: waitpid() syscall
        WaitingIO --> [*]: I/O complete
        Sleeping --> [*]: Timer wakeup
        WaitingChild --> [*]: Child exits
    }

    %% Annotations
    note left of RUNNING
        Preemption points:
        • Timer interrupt (every 1ms)
        • Voluntary yield()
        • Higher priority process
    end note

    note left of BLOCKED
        Blocking operations:
        • read() on empty buffer
        • write() on full buffer
        • sleep() syscall
        • waitpid() on running child
    end note
